1
00:01:41,335 --> 00:01:44,270
The man who said,
"I'd rather be lucky than good,"

2
00:01:44,338 --> 00:01:46,533
saw deeply into life.

3
00:01:46,741 --> 00:01:50,541
People are afraid to face how great
a part of life is dependent on luck.

4
00:01:51,379 --> 00:01:54,610
It's scary to think so much
is out of one's control.

5
00:01:55,449 --> 00:01:59,408
There are moments in a match
when the ball hits the top of the net,

6
00:01:59,720 --> 00:02:04,248
and for a split second
it can either go forward or fall back.

7
00:02:05,226 --> 00:02:09,162
With a little luck,
it goes forward and you win.

8
00:02:09,230 --> 00:02:12,667
Or maybe it doesn't, and you lose.

9
00:02:16,939 --> 00:02:18,531
Sorry.

10
00:02:23,612 --> 00:02:25,546
Mr. Townsend.

11
00:02:30,686 --> 00:02:32,677
Just this way.

12
00:02:33,422 --> 00:02:35,913
So the Beach Olub Marbella,
tennis instructor.

13
00:02:35,991 --> 00:02:39,483
Stanford House.
Forte Village, Sardinia. Nice.

14
00:02:39,561 --> 00:02:41,552
Yes. I've had
a good deal of experience.

15
00:02:41,630 --> 00:02:43,154
Yeah, so I see.

16
00:02:43,231 --> 00:02:46,291
Now, I've heard very good things.
You don't miss playing professionally?

17
00:02:46,368 --> 00:02:48,097
I thank God every day
I don't have to do it.

18
00:02:48,170 --> 00:02:51,503
I hate the whole tennis tour thing.

19
00:02:51,573 --> 00:02:55,907
Oonstant traveling, and I was
never going to be Rusedski or Agassi.

20
00:02:55,978 --> 00:02:57,775
You have to really want it.

21
00:02:57,846 --> 00:02:59,746
Not that I have their talent.

22
00:03:00,215 --> 00:03:02,912
Well, your credentials
and references are excellent.

23
00:03:02,986 --> 00:03:04,817
And you want to live in London?

24
00:03:04,887 --> 00:03:07,947
Very much. Very much.

25
00:03:08,024 --> 00:03:11,255
We have a very
exclusive membership here.

26
00:03:11,327 --> 00:03:13,192
You can begin this weekend?

27
00:03:14,063 --> 00:03:16,657
Thank you. Thank you very much.

28
00:03:17,900 --> 00:03:20,801
That's your sofa,
which also doubles up as a bed.

29
00:03:20,870 --> 00:03:23,668
Which is great, you know,
'cause you can be watching some telly,

30
00:03:23,740 --> 00:03:25,799
ain't got the hassle
of having to go to a bedroom.

31
00:03:25,875 --> 00:03:28,241
You can just open it up, get your kip.

32
00:03:28,311 --> 00:03:30,472
Kitchen just through there.

33
00:03:30,546 --> 00:03:33,947
All your amenities, fixtures,
fittings, washer-dryer...

34
00:03:34,017 --> 00:03:35,279
All that stuff.

35
00:03:35,351 --> 00:03:37,819
Lovely view, not overlooked.

36
00:03:37,887 --> 00:03:39,821
So it's all good.

37
00:03:39,889 --> 00:03:42,414
This is 225 a week?

38
00:03:42,492 --> 00:03:46,189
Well, it's London, mate. Bang, mate.
If you don't like it, move to Leeds.

39
00:03:46,262 --> 00:03:48,059
D'you know what I mean?
You got a wok?

40
00:03:48,131 --> 00:03:50,929
You got a wok? It's one of those
Oriental, sort of conical pans.

41
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:53,162
- No, no, no.
- The geezer who was in here before,

42
00:03:53,237 --> 00:03:56,229
he left one in there. You're
welcome to it. I'll throw that in.

43
00:03:56,306 --> 00:03:59,070
- I'll take it.
- That's a good choice.

44
00:04:14,091 --> 00:04:15,615
Very good.

45
00:04:28,305 --> 00:04:29,772
Ohris Wilton.

46
00:04:29,840 --> 00:04:31,637
This is Tom Hewett.

47
00:04:31,708 --> 00:04:33,642
- Very nice to meet you. How do you do?
- Morning. Pleasure.

48
00:04:33,710 --> 00:04:35,439
I think Ohris would be
the perfect instructor for you,

49
00:04:35,512 --> 00:04:38,208
and he's very patient.
Great at analyzing a player's faults.

50
00:04:38,282 --> 00:04:41,479
I'm so out of practice. I mean,
I haven't played since university,

51
00:04:41,552 --> 00:04:44,818
and I loved it, but I haven't
picked up a racket in bloody ages, so...

52
00:04:44,889 --> 00:04:46,413
Don't worry, it comes back.

53
00:04:46,491 --> 00:04:49,119
What you can't do is rush in,
be discouraged.

54
00:04:49,194 --> 00:04:50,491
OK.

55
00:04:50,562 --> 00:04:52,621
- Well, good luck.
- Thank you very much.

56
00:04:52,697 --> 00:04:54,790
- Over here.
- Brilliant.

57
00:05:06,644 --> 00:05:10,580
OK, so who was better, or tougher?
Henman or Agassi?

58
00:05:10,648 --> 00:05:12,946
- They were both great.
- Yeah, I know, but I mean,

59
00:05:13,017 --> 00:05:14,882
you held your own more than admirably.

60
00:05:14,953 --> 00:05:16,352
For a while.

61
00:05:16,421 --> 00:05:18,946
But as the game goes on,
you see how really good they are.

62
00:05:19,023 --> 00:05:20,786
- Actually, I'll get this.
- No, no, no, no.

63
00:05:20,859 --> 00:05:23,350
- No, please, Tom, I insist. I insist.
- No, no, no, no, no.

64
00:05:23,428 --> 00:05:25,293
Get your dirty great forehand off.

65
00:05:26,764 --> 00:05:28,698
Thank you. I'll get the next one.

66
00:05:29,634 --> 00:05:31,568
So, do you need a lift after this?

67
00:05:31,636 --> 00:05:35,231
Actually, I'm looking for a music store.
I want to buy some ODs.

68
00:05:35,306 --> 00:05:39,004
Music around here?
I think there's one on the Fulham Road.

69
00:05:39,078 --> 00:05:41,171
And they'll have a decent opera section?

70
00:05:41,247 --> 00:05:43,306
Opera? You like opera, really?

71
00:05:43,382 --> 00:05:44,610
I love opera.

72
00:05:44,683 --> 00:05:47,811
Papa gives loads
to the Royal in Oovent Garden.

73
00:05:47,887 --> 00:05:49,787
I know this is gonna sound a bit weird,

74
00:05:49,855 --> 00:05:52,187
but would you like to go
to the opera tomorrow night?

75
00:05:53,526 --> 00:05:55,255
To the opera?

76
00:05:55,327 --> 00:05:57,795
Yeah. We've got a box
and someone's not coming.

77
00:05:57,863 --> 00:06:00,331
It's La bloody Traviata.

78
00:06:00,399 --> 00:06:03,459
My God. I'd love to.

79
00:06:03,536 --> 00:06:06,403
Are you sure it's not an imposition?
Oan I at least pay for my seat?

80
00:06:06,472 --> 00:06:09,066
It's not an imposition,
it'd be an absolute pleasure.

81
00:06:09,141 --> 00:06:13,305
I just like the fact that we both
share a love for opera. Brilliant.

82
00:06:15,414 --> 00:06:16,403
So?

83
00:06:16,482 --> 00:06:19,474
- I said to David and Melissa...
- Evening all. Hello, Mum.

84
00:06:19,552 --> 00:06:21,611
Hello, sweetie. Very nice to see you.

85
00:06:21,687 --> 00:06:24,520
- This is Ohris. This is my father Alec.
- Hello. Good to meet you.

86
00:06:24,590 --> 00:06:26,524
I hear you're an
incredible tennis player.

87
00:06:26,592 --> 00:06:29,357
I played once, and then I gave up,
then I went back, then I gave up,

88
00:06:29,429 --> 00:06:30,623
- then I went back
- Rubbish.

89
00:06:30,697 --> 00:06:33,359
- I'm sure Tom exaggerated my game.
- I just got bored.

90
00:06:33,433 --> 00:06:35,458
- Good evening. My pleasure.
- Nice to meet you.

91
00:06:35,535 --> 00:06:38,095
- This is my sister... Ohloe.
- There's a chair somewhere.

92
00:06:38,171 --> 00:06:40,230
- I'm Ohloe. Nice to meet you.
- There's two more.

93
00:07:30,691 --> 00:07:34,627
Yeah, well, the olds say thank you
very much for the lovely flowers.

94
00:07:34,695 --> 00:07:37,823
They said it was very thoughtful,
and totally unnecessary.

95
00:07:37,898 --> 00:07:42,267
But off the record, well done, A plus,
'cause they love that sort of thing.

96
00:07:42,336 --> 00:07:45,897
Oh, they're lovely people.
And your sister's very bright.

97
00:07:45,973 --> 00:07:48,635
Frighteningly so at times. But...

98
00:07:48,709 --> 00:07:51,701
Anyway, she thought you were terrific,
and she wanted to invite you

99
00:07:51,779 --> 00:07:54,680
to our country house
with the parents on Sunday.

100
00:07:54,749 --> 00:07:57,718
'Oause they're having a party,
there'll be some good people.

101
00:07:57,785 --> 00:08:02,119
And I'll play you some great music,
because Dad's got an epic collection.

102
00:08:20,475 --> 00:08:22,340
Ohlo-Ohlo, do you wanna have
a knock with Ohris for a bit?

103
00:08:22,411 --> 00:08:24,276
It's just that
it's 5:00 somewhere, darling,

104
00:08:24,346 --> 00:08:26,507
and I've some serious
cocktails to start making.

105
00:08:26,581 --> 00:08:29,607
Irish! Have you ever had a
Ouba libre or a caipirinha?

106
00:08:29,685 --> 00:08:32,119
Lt'd be really boring
for Ohris to play with me on my own.

107
00:08:32,187 --> 00:08:34,917
It's really boring for him
to play with me, but he's a good sport.

108
00:08:34,990 --> 00:08:37,788
And anyway, you've got better
legs than I've got. Ohop-chop.

109
00:08:37,859 --> 00:08:40,828
Don't be silly. I teach people
who have never held a racket before.

110
00:08:40,896 --> 00:08:43,763
- I'm so bad.
- That's how you get better.

111
00:08:43,832 --> 00:08:45,663
Playing with a stronger player. Oome on.

112
00:08:45,734 --> 00:08:47,463
OK.

113
00:09:07,423 --> 00:09:08,720
Was I dreadful?

114
00:09:08,791 --> 00:09:11,555
Not at all.
You have a very unique style.

115
00:09:11,627 --> 00:09:15,529
Yeah, it's called clumsy.
How did you get to be so good anyway?

116
00:09:15,598 --> 00:09:17,930
Tom says you played
with some of the real greats.

117
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:20,867
For me, it was a way out
of a poor existence.

118
00:09:20,937 --> 00:09:23,929
Oaught the eye of a good coach.
I don't know.

119
00:09:25,041 --> 00:09:27,032
It all came so easy at first.

120
00:09:27,410 --> 00:09:29,674
- Do you enjoy teaching?
- Not really.

121
00:09:30,146 --> 00:09:31,670
I mean, it's OK for now,

122
00:09:31,748 --> 00:09:34,478
but I'd cut my throat
if I thought I had to do it forever.

123
00:09:34,550 --> 00:09:36,381
I'd like to do something with my life.

124
00:09:36,452 --> 00:09:40,047
You know, special.
I'd like to make a contribution.

125
00:09:40,123 --> 00:09:43,354
So, you're a poor boy
from Ireland come to London.

126
00:09:43,726 --> 00:09:45,159
I love it.

127
00:09:45,228 --> 00:09:47,628
It's so exciting and alive.

128
00:09:47,697 --> 00:09:50,029
I've never seen so much art or theater.

129
00:09:50,099 --> 00:09:52,294
Not that I've taken
much advantage of it yet.

130
00:09:52,368 --> 00:09:55,031
Well, look, if you'd like someone
to show you around,

131
00:09:55,105 --> 00:09:58,836
I grew up in Belgravia. I'd be happy
to take you to all the good places.

132
00:09:58,909 --> 00:10:00,137
That'd be great.

133
00:10:00,444 --> 00:10:04,175
On one condition: I buy the tickets.

134
00:10:04,248 --> 00:10:06,011
Oh, dear, is that going to be an issue?

135
00:10:06,083 --> 00:10:08,813
I'm afraid it is.
I'm very old-fashioned.

136
00:10:08,886 --> 00:10:11,582
But actually,
I did read something about the...

137
00:10:11,655 --> 00:10:13,953
...exhibition in the Saatchi Gallery.

138
00:10:14,024 --> 00:10:17,892
That's perfect.
It'd be my pleasure to take you.

139
00:10:17,961 --> 00:10:20,156
You're very kind to offer this.

140
00:10:20,230 --> 00:10:22,630
Oan I at least give you
some free tennis lessons?

141
00:10:22,699 --> 00:10:24,394
OK, it's a deal.

142
00:10:24,468 --> 00:10:26,868
How about Wednesday for the Saatchi?

143
00:10:26,937 --> 00:10:28,427
I can do that.

144
00:10:28,505 --> 00:10:31,963
- Shall we meet for lunch first?
- It's a date.

145
00:10:32,042 --> 00:10:34,772
I'd better get ready.
Your guests will be arriving soon.

146
00:10:34,845 --> 00:10:36,745
Yeah, yeah. Of course. Go.

147
00:10:36,814 --> 00:10:40,011
A sweaty tennis player's
hardly what they expect.

148
00:11:36,441 --> 00:11:39,775
So who's my next victim?

149
00:11:41,013 --> 00:11:42,105
You?

150
00:11:42,715 --> 00:11:44,706
I haven't played table tennis
in quite a while.

151
00:11:45,551 --> 00:11:48,281
Would you like to play
for a thousand pounds a game?

152
00:11:50,089 --> 00:11:51,716
What did I walk into?

153
00:12:02,768 --> 00:12:05,066
What did I walk into?

154
00:12:06,405 --> 00:12:08,396
It's like this.

155
00:12:09,141 --> 00:12:11,200
- May I?
- Please.

156
00:12:12,978 --> 00:12:17,438
You have to lean in,
and hit through the ball.

157
00:12:20,386 --> 00:12:23,287
I was doing just fine
until you showed up.

158
00:12:23,355 --> 00:12:25,516
The story of my life.

159
00:12:25,591 --> 00:12:27,024
So, tell me,

160
00:12:27,092 --> 00:12:29,891
what's a beautiful, young,
American Ping-Pong player doing

161
00:12:29,963 --> 00:12:32,193
mingling amongst
the British upper class?

162
00:12:37,003 --> 00:12:41,337
Did anyone ever tell you,
you play a very aggressive game?

163
00:12:44,010 --> 00:12:46,911
Did anyone ever tell you
you've very sensual lips?

164
00:12:51,117 --> 00:12:54,314
- Extremely aggressive.
- I'm naturally competitive.

165
00:12:55,388 --> 00:12:57,379
Is it off-putting?

166
00:12:59,326 --> 00:13:01,817
I'll have to think
about that for a while.

167
00:13:05,298 --> 00:13:06,390
There you are.

168
00:13:06,466 --> 00:13:08,525
I wanted to introduce you
to Ohris Wilton.

169
00:13:08,602 --> 00:13:11,628
Ohris Wilton,
this is Nola Rice, my fiancee.

170
00:13:13,506 --> 00:13:15,906
So, you're the tennis pro.

171
00:13:15,976 --> 00:13:17,967
- Hello, darling.
- My pleasure.

172
00:13:18,044 --> 00:13:20,376
He was trying to have
his way with me over the table.

173
00:13:20,447 --> 00:13:23,246
Oh, really? Yeah, well,
you'd better watch out for this one.

174
00:13:23,317 --> 00:13:25,342
He's made a living out of hustling.

175
00:13:25,720 --> 00:13:28,416
I'll be ready for you next time.

176
00:13:30,291 --> 00:13:33,818
- I'll see you outside.
- Oh, yeah.

177
00:13:40,635 --> 00:13:42,933
She's quite something, isn't she?

178
00:13:45,039 --> 00:13:48,133
- How long have you been together?
- Six months.

179
00:13:48,209 --> 00:13:50,302
Jesus, yeah, six months!

180
00:13:50,378 --> 00:13:52,812
She came over to study acting,
and I met her at a party

181
00:13:52,880 --> 00:13:54,973
that I'd crashed
and she'd crashed, and...

182
00:13:55,049 --> 00:13:57,711
...one thing led to another.

183
00:13:58,486 --> 00:14:01,478
Obviously, it's taken Mother quite
a long time to get used to the idea

184
00:14:01,555 --> 00:14:03,079
that I'm serious about her, but...

185
00:14:03,157 --> 00:14:04,146
To be honest with you,

186
00:14:04,225 --> 00:14:06,523
Mother's always had
this funny little agenda for me

187
00:14:06,594 --> 00:14:09,859
which doesn't really involve
marrying a struggling actress.

188
00:14:09,930 --> 00:14:12,023
Especially an American one.

189
00:14:13,635 --> 00:14:16,001
But I am crazy about her.

190
00:14:16,071 --> 00:14:19,768
Anyway, I think we should all go to
dinner next week. What do you think?

191
00:14:19,941 --> 00:14:21,841
- I'd love to.
- Excellent.

192
00:14:21,910 --> 00:14:25,437
Now, Irish, how about a little drop
of Scottish before supper?

193
00:14:25,514 --> 00:14:28,847
- Why not.
- Lead on. Quickly.

194
00:15:08,691 --> 00:15:11,319
These afternoons have been great.

195
00:15:12,095 --> 00:15:15,326
I'm so glad your schedule
allows you so much time off.

196
00:15:15,398 --> 00:15:16,990
Yes, it's fun.

197
00:15:17,066 --> 00:15:19,728
Although it wouldn't hurt
to have a few more pupils.

198
00:15:21,971 --> 00:15:23,962
Do you need money?

199
00:15:24,040 --> 00:15:25,837
God, no.

200
00:15:26,109 --> 00:15:27,701
No, I'm fine.

201
00:15:27,777 --> 00:15:30,473
It's very sweet of you to ask,
but I don't.

202
00:15:36,652 --> 00:15:40,144
I'm only asking
because I care about you.

203
00:15:57,875 --> 00:16:00,708
Shall we go to your place or mine?

204
00:16:00,778 --> 00:16:03,042
I don't think mine's
quite what you're used to.

205
00:16:03,113 --> 00:16:07,015
Shut up. I think yours'll be just great.

206
00:16:26,804 --> 00:16:30,331
You've been seeing a lot
of Ohris Wilton lately, I understand.

207
00:16:30,407 --> 00:16:34,002
- Yeah. He's very nice.
- I liked him.

208
00:16:34,077 --> 00:16:36,841
I just don't understand
what he's aiming for.

209
00:16:36,914 --> 00:16:39,781
He certainly doesn't want to be
a tennis pro for the rest of his life.

210
00:16:39,850 --> 00:16:42,114
Well, I find him very likeable.

211
00:16:42,186 --> 00:16:45,644
He's fought his way up the only way
open to him, and he's not trivial.

212
00:16:45,722 --> 00:16:49,989
I had a very interesting conversation
the other day about Dostoyevsky.

213
00:16:50,061 --> 00:16:52,052
Oan't we do something for him?

214
00:16:52,130 --> 00:16:54,428
A place in one of
your companies or something?

215
00:16:54,499 --> 00:16:55,796
Has he expressed a desire?

216
00:16:55,867 --> 00:16:59,530
No, but... he's open,
you know, about his future.

217
00:16:59,604 --> 00:17:01,834
He really wants
to make something of his life.

218
00:17:01,906 --> 00:17:03,965
Ohloe, be careful.

219
00:17:04,042 --> 00:17:07,978
Tom's involved with a woman I have
reservations about. Don't rush off.

220
00:17:08,046 --> 00:17:10,947
Tom's happy with Nola.
You're prejudiced 'cause she's American.

221
00:17:11,015 --> 00:17:12,880
She's spoilt and temperamental.

222
00:17:12,951 --> 00:17:14,816
She's an actress, they're emotional.

223
00:17:14,886 --> 00:17:18,117
She's deluding herself, and she's moody.
She's not right for Tom.

224
00:17:18,189 --> 00:17:21,420
Well, I care very deeply for Ohris,
and I think he feels the same way.

225
00:17:21,492 --> 00:17:23,858
- Who are you talking about?
- Nola.

226
00:17:36,641 --> 00:17:38,973
- Have you been waiting ages?
- Hello. Not at all.

227
00:17:39,043 --> 00:17:41,535
Traffic was awful.
The others'll be here in a minute.

228
00:17:41,614 --> 00:17:43,479
They're probably
stuck in it somewhere.

229
00:17:43,549 --> 00:17:45,483
Oan I have a champagne cocktail, please?

230
00:17:47,686 --> 00:17:51,747
One of your father's associates spoke to
me today about the possibility of a job.

231
00:17:51,824 --> 00:17:53,416
Did you say anything?

232
00:17:53,492 --> 00:17:57,861
Look, I just told Papa to keep his
eyes open if anything juicy opened up,

233
00:17:57,930 --> 00:18:00,763
so you could have first option,
if you wanted it.

234
00:18:01,267 --> 00:18:03,531
- You're not cross, are you?
- God, no.

