170
01:08:46,156 --> 01:08:47,987
- Why did they do that?
- 'Oause it howls all night long.

171
01:08:48,058 --> 01:08:49,582
- Yes, I'm sure it can.
- Oh, that's mean.

172
01:08:49,659 --> 01:08:51,422
I know. And it's
terribly small and furry.

173
01:08:51,494 --> 01:08:52,483
That's mean.

174
01:08:53,063 --> 01:08:55,588
I think tomorrow
we should go for a morning ride.

175
01:08:55,665 --> 01:08:57,132
I've some lovely new horses.

176
01:08:57,200 --> 01:08:58,792
Do you remember when
Ohris came here first,

177
01:08:58,868 --> 01:09:00,836
and he had some
serious qualms about riding?

178
01:09:00,904 --> 01:09:01,996
- I spoke to Teddy.
- How is he?

179
01:09:02,072 --> 01:09:03,903
Well, this morning he was talking
about buying a horse of his own.

180
01:09:03,973 --> 01:09:05,565
- No.
- Yeah.

181
01:09:05,642 --> 01:09:07,166
I don't know, it was all in good fun.

182
01:09:07,243 --> 01:09:08,369
- Where from?
- Anyway...

183
01:09:08,445 --> 01:09:10,845
- I think Nan's got a really nice mare.
