I'm trying to make it for tomorrow.

194
01:09:37,040 --> 01:09:39,133
I can't wait till tomorrow,
I'm going crazy.

195
01:09:39,209 --> 01:09:42,042
- What the hell's the matter?
- I'm pregnant.

196
01:09:48,218 --> 01:09:50,209
I'll talk to you tomorrow.

197
01:09:50,286 --> 01:09:52,754
'Oause we've got to go
and try and look at this...

198
01:09:52,822 --> 01:09:55,916
...horse for Ohris.
- They got it in the navy?

199
01:09:56,693 --> 01:09:59,628
Yeah, the... It was lack of enough
vegetables, or something.

200
01:09:59,696 --> 01:10:02,221
I wonder if that's why they took
lemons and oranges...

201
01:10:02,298 --> 01:10:03,629
Well, they only had biscuits.

202
01:10:03,700 --> 01:10:06,066
Well, that's where
Rose's Lime Oordial originated...

203
01:10:06,136 --> 01:10:09,902
- Who keeps calling?
- It was Samantha, my secretary.

204
01:10:09,973 --> 01:10:13,101
I'm afraid I won't be able
to go riding tomorrow. I can't help it.

205
01:10:13,176 --> 01:10:15,440
I thought Samantha said she was
going to her parents this weekend.

206
01:10:15,512 --> 01:10:17,776
I know, it's all my fault. Poor girl.

207
01:10:18,681 --> 01:10:20,012
It's no big deal.

208
01:10:20,083 --> 01:10:21,243
I'll pop back into town.

209
01:10:21,384 --> 01:10:25,343
The whole thing'll take a few hours,
and it'll be off my mind. I promise.

210
01:10:25,421 --> 01:10:27,082
- That's a shame.
- It's really sad.

211
01:10:27,157 --> 01:10:28,784
Well, it is a pity because I...

212
01:10:28,858 --> 01:10:31,053
