01:51:03,157 --> 01:51:05,421
I didn't want the
sexual relationship to end,

777
01:51:05,492 --> 01:51:07,551
but I'm not gonna break up my home.

778
01:51:09,296 --> 01:51:12,231
My wife and I are
trying very hard to have a baby.

779
01:51:12,299 --> 01:51:15,962
We've seen several
fertility doctors, et cetera.

780
01:51:17,037 --> 01:51:20,666
You can check that out if you like,
but I beg you to be discreet.

781
01:51:20,741 --> 01:51:22,766
But you did lead her on,

782
01:51:22,843 --> 01:51:25,641
so that she had the impression
you were unhappy at home.

783
01:51:26,313 --> 01:51:28,611
I tried to tip-toe around it
and not lead her on,

784
01:51:28,682 --> 01:51:31,446
but she's going to believe
what she wants to believe.

785
01:51:32,319 --> 01:51:37,757
Look, don't irresponsibly run roughshod
over this and wreck people's lives.

786
01:51:38,392 --> 01:51:41,259
I mean, there is no case
because I would not harm anyone,

787
01:51:41,328 --> 01:51:43,421
much less Nola Rice.

788
01:51:48,769 --> 01:51:51,670
Isn't it obvious
that somebody killed her neighbor,

789
01:51:51,739 --> 01:51:53,764
and she walked in when it was happening?

790
01:51:55,643 --> 01:51:59,170
God, I beg you, don't go on
a fishing expedition over this and...

791
01:51:59,580 --> 01:52:01,571
...wreck people's lives.

792
01:52:01,649 --> 01:52:04,743
My family, my marriage is at stake.

793
01:52:05,819 --> 01:52:08,447
We just have to
check out everything in a murder case.

794
01:52:08,522 --> 01:52:10,922
OK, but I'm not your man.

795
01:52:11,425 --> 01:52:14,656
I know it's not the most
honorable thing to cheat on your wife,

796
01:52:14,728 --> 01:52:16,958
but that does not make me a murderer.

797
01:52:17,131 --> 01:52:20,066
We're... obligated
to review the situation.

798
01:52:20,134 --> 01:52:22,125
I understand
it's sensitive stuff for you.

799
01:52:22,202 --> 01:52:23,794
And if we have to talk to you again,

800
01:52:23,871 --> 01:52:26,203
we'll do everything in our power
to keep it very private.

801
01:52:26,273 --> 01:52:27,797
Your personal life's your own.

802
01:52:27,875 --> 01:52:31,743
We're not making any moral judgments,
just investigating a crime.

803
01:52:41,922 --> 01:52:44,015
I understand.

804
01:52:44,925 --> 01:52:46,586
Look...

805
01:52:46,660 --> 01:52:48,855
...if you have to get
in contact with me again,

806
01:52:48,929 --> 01:52:50,920
which, God in heaven,
I hope you don't,

807
01:52:50,998 --> 01:52:52,966
please call me on my mobile.

808
01:52:53,400 --> 01:52:55,459
This is my number.

809
01:52:57,337 --> 01:52:58,929
Thanks.

810
01:52:59,640 --> 01:53:00,629
One other thing.

811
01:53:00,708 --> 01:53:03,108
Do you own or have access to a shotgun?

812
01:53:05,279 --> 01:53:06,746
Me?

813
01:53:06,947 --> 01:53:08,141
No.

814
01:53:08,215 --> 01:53:12,083
My father-in-law shoots
on the estate, but not me.

815
01:53:12,152 --> 01:53:14,347
You can check it out, but...

816
01:53:15,322 --> 01:53:19,281
...I beg you to consider mine
and his position.

817
01:53:19,359 --> 01:53:21,452
Of course.

818
01:53:24,431 --> 01:53:26,422
Thank you.

819
01:53:35,042 --> 01:53:37,033
So, what do you think?

820
01:53:37,578 --> 01:53:39,375
I think it's what it looks like.

821
01:53:39,446 --> 01:53:41,505
Someone robbed and killed Mrs. Eastby,

822
01:53:41,582 --> 01:53:45,143
who was surprised leaving,
and killed Nola Rice.

823
01:53:46,153 --> 01:53:49,748
Yeah, I know. I know, it's got
drug robbery written all over it.

824
01:53:49,823 --> 01:53:51,814
He's 'specting a baby.

825
01:53:51,992 --> 01:53:54,426
OK, he's not gonna win
a medal for fidelity, but...

826
01:53:55,562 --> 01:53:57,189
...we can find out discreetly enough

827
01:53:57,264 --> 01:54:00,256
whether the Hewetts
had a shotgun unaccounted for.

828
01:54:02,136 --> 01:54:06,197
I don't think that he would know the
first thing about stealing one though,

829
01:54:06,273 --> 01:54:09,106
never mind sawing one off.

830
01:54:09,910 --> 01:54:12,902
It's a bit of a stretch.
He's got no previous convictions.

831
01:54:12,980 --> 01:54:14,709
Not even a speeding ticket.

832
01:54:14,782 --> 01:54:17,580
The coroner says
that Eastby was killed first.

833
01:54:17,651 --> 01:54:19,983
- Yeah.
- There's no sign of a forced entry.

834
01:54:20,053 --> 01:54:22,283
So Mrs. Eastby knew the killer,
if she let him in.

835
01:54:22,356 --> 01:54:23,846
Well, come on, Mike.

836
01:54:23,924 --> 01:54:25,755
Ninety percent
of the crimes we go out on,

837
01:54:25,826 --> 01:54:27,987
people open their doors
and invite the criminals in.

838
01:54:28,061 --> 01:54:30,359
Yeah, I know, you're right.
I'm just thinking out loud.

839
01:54:30,430 --> 01:54:33,422
- It's just he's got a real motive.
- Yeah, maybe.

840
01:54:33,500 --> 01:54:38,096
But a motive, as you and I
both painfully know, is not a case.

841
01:54:38,172 --> 01:54:41,198
I'm torn because the Rice murder
was clearly an afterthought,

842
01:54:41,275 --> 01:54:43,140
but I'd love to pursue it a little more.

843
01:54:43,210 --> 01:54:46,577
But I'm reluctant to fish around
and cause problems for everybody.

844
01:54:46,647 --> 01:54:48,945
Well, if something develops,
we can pursue it.

845
01:54:49,016 --> 01:54:51,746
I doubt anything's
gonna drop into our laps.

846
01:56:49,503 --> 01:56:51,164
Ohris.

847
01:57:01,148 --> 01:57:02,877
Nola...

848
01:57:04,952 --> 01:57:07,216
...it wasn't easy.

849
01:57:08,188 --> 01:57:10,952
But when the time came,
I could pull the trigger.

850
01:57:12,859 --> 01:57:15,851
You never know who your neighbors are
till there's a crisis.

851
01:57:17,464 --> 01:57:21,662
You can learn to push the guilt
under the rug and... go on.

852
01:57:22,836 --> 01:57:24,599
You have to.

853
01:57:24,671 --> 01:57:27,196
Otherwise it overwhelms you.

854
01:57:27,274 --> 01:57:29,435
And what about me?

855
01:57:29,509 --> 01:57:32,239
What about the next-door neighbor?

856
01:57:33,013 --> 01:57:36,005
I had no involvement
in this awful affair.

857
01:57:37,451 --> 01:57:42,354
Is there no problem about me
having to die as an innocent bystander?

858
01:57:44,291 --> 01:57:48,694
The innocent are sometimes slain
to make way for a grander scheme.

859
01:57:50,764 --> 01:57:53,028
You were collateral damage.

860
01:57:53,100 --> 01:57:55,568
So was your own child.

861
01:57:59,806 --> 01:58:01,797
Sophocles said:

862
01:58:03,276 --> 01:58:05,471
"To never have been born

863
01:58:06,079 --> 01:58:08,570
may be the greatest boon of all."

864
01:58:10,917 --> 01:58:13,249
Prepare to pay the price, Ohris.

865
01:58:14,154 --> 01:58:16,315
Your actions were clumsy.

866
01:58:16,390 --> 01:58:18,085
Full of holes.

867
01:58:18,158 --> 01:58:21,355
Almost like someone
begging to be found out.

868
01:58:24,865 --> 01:58:27,834
It would be fitting
if I were apprehended

869
01:58:27,901 --> 01:58:29,801
and punished.

870
01:58:30,937 --> 01:58:34,668
At least there would be
some small sign ofjustice.

871
01:58:34,741 --> 01:58:37,710
Some small...

872
01:58:38,412 --> 01:58:41,848
...measure of hope
for the possibility of meaning.

873
01:58:44,251 --> 01:58:47,414
Ohris Wilton killed them.
I see how he did it.

874
01:58:47,487 --> 01:58:49,250
What?

875
01:58:50,457 --> 01:58:52,015
It's as we speculated

876
01:58:52,092 --> 01:58:54,492
and said was too elaborate,
but that's what he did.

877
01:58:54,561 --> 01:58:57,655
He killed the next-door neighbor first
to throw us off the scent

878
01:58:57,731 --> 01:58:59,426
and set up the appearance of a robbery.

879
01:58:59,499 --> 01:59:00,488
He waited in the hall.

880
01:59:00,567 --> 01:59:02,467
He knew she'd be back
the same time as usual,

881
01:59:02,536 --> 01:59:05,801
and he killed her, making it seem like
she surprised a burglar running out.

882
01:59:05,872 --> 01:59:07,999
He planned it all so he could
make the theater in time

883
01:59:08,075 --> 01:59:10,339
to strengthen his alibi,
if one became necessary.

884
01:59:10,410 --> 01:59:12,935
Now, I haven't figured out
the weapon problem,

885
01:59:13,013 --> 01:59:14,480
and I know it's a lot to ask a jury,

886
01:59:14,548 --> 01:59:16,743
but the correctness of it
came to me in my sleep

887
01:59:16,817 --> 01:59:18,580
and I am going to break this case.

888
01:59:18,652 --> 01:59:20,483
I hate to be the bearer
of bad news, Mike.

889
01:59:20,554 --> 01:59:21,543
What?

890
01:59:21,621 --> 01:59:23,555
Not that your dream
isn't of primary interest to a jury.

891
01:59:23,623 --> 01:59:24,885
What's the bad news?

892
01:59:24,958 --> 01:59:27,859
There was another shooting
in the area last night, 4am.

893
01:59:27,928 --> 01:59:30,658
A drug addict killed.
Looks like a drug sale turned nasty.

894
01:59:30,730 --> 01:59:33,961
What, and he confessed
to killing two women before he died?

895
01:59:34,034 --> 01:59:35,729
No, he didn't have to.

896
01:59:35,802 --> 01:59:38,999
The old woman's wedding ring
was right in his pocket.

897
01:59:39,673 --> 01:59:42,938
- No.
- Name and date engraved right on it.

898
01:59:43,910 --> 01:59:47,141
- I don't believe it.
- I know. I know.

899
01:59:47,214 --> 01:59:49,512
Your case looked good, lots of motive.

900
01:59:49,583 --> 01:59:51,847
But his motive
was pretty strong too. Heroin.

901
01:59:52,185 --> 01:59:54,551
Junkie with a long string
of convictions.

902
01:59:55,155 --> 01:59:57,180
Killed by one of his own, no doubt.

903
01:59:57,257 --> 01:59:59,088
Oome on, I'll buy you breakfast.

904
01:59:59,159 --> 02:00:01,491
You can traumatize me
with the rest of your dreams.

905
02:00:01,561 --> 02:00:02,960
No, wait.

906
02:00:03,029 --> 02:00:07,022
What if Wilton did it, threw the
jewels away, this guy finds them?

907
02:00:08,435 --> 02:00:11,802
I don't know.
See what tonight's dream tells you.

908
02:00:11,872 --> 02:00:14,602
I'm sure a jury will be interested.

909
02:00:14,674 --> 02:00:16,539
Oome on.

910
02:00:17,878 --> 02:00:19,140
I give up.

911
02:00:19,212 --> 02:00:21,009
I knew Wilton didn't do it.

912
02:00:21,081 --> 02:00:23,413
He's another poor schmuck
who cheated on his wife.

913
02:00:23,483 --> 02:00:26,816
When you see those pictures
of Nola Rice, you can see why though.

914
02:00:27,521 --> 02:00:30,285
What a world. Am I right?

915
02:00:30,757 --> 02:00:33,749
Oareful, careful.
I'm always afraid they'll drop.

916
02:00:33,827 --> 02:00:36,819
- Oh, chill out, Dad.
- Babies are so, so soft.

917
02:00:36,897 --> 02:00:38,831
Right. Ohampagne.

918
02:00:38,899 --> 02:00:41,129
- I think he's got your eyes, Ohloe.
- Really?

919
02:00:41,201 --> 02:00:43,567
I think he's got
your coloring darling, I really do.

920
02:00:43,637 --> 02:00:46,902
Mummy, you can't tell anything yet.
They change all the time.

921
02:00:48,241 --> 02:00:49,799
- My nephew.
- Uncle, Uncle Tom.

922
02:00:49,876 --> 02:00:52,538
- Oh, look at these flowers.
- No, he does look like Ohristopher.

923
02:00:52,612 --> 02:00:56,104
Actually, speaking of which, didn't you
move into Alan Sinclair's old office?

924
02:00:56,183 --> 02:00:58,549
- You lucky swine.
- Oh, Mummy, look, he's dreaming.

925
02:00:58,618 --> 02:01:00,108
Let's work on number two. Oome on.

926
02:01:00,187 --> 02:01:03,520
Oome on, he is a handsome boy.
Look at that face.

927
02:01:03,590 --> 02:01:04,852
Yeah, he's gorgeous.

928
02:01:04,925 --> 02:01:06,984
Right, here we are. Eleanor. Please...

929
02:01:07,060 --> 02:01:08,391
- Ohloe...
- Good stuff, Papa.

930
02:01:08,461 --> 02:01:09,985
- Thank you, darling. There you are.
- There we go.

931
02:01:10,063 --> 02:01:12,190
- It's all right, you stay there.
- I'll pass them round, shall I?

932
02:01:12,265 --> 02:01:13,254
Please do.

933
02:01:13,333 --> 02:01:14,391
- What a good idea.
- Darling, have one.

934
02:01:14,467 --> 02:01:16,697
- To Terence Elliot Wilton.
- Yes.

935
02:01:16,770 --> 02:01:19,170
With parents like Ohloe and Ohris,

936
02:01:19,239 --> 02:01:22,037
this child will be great
at anything he sets his mind to.

937
02:01:22,108 --> 02:01:23,632
- Thank you, Mummy.
- He will. He...

938
02:01:23,710 --> 02:01:25,644
Do you know what,
I don't care if he's great.

939
02:01:25,712 --> 02:01:27,043
I just hope that he's lucky.

940
02:01:27,113 --> 02:01:28,740
- Oh, lovely.
- What a lovely thought.

941
02:01:28,815 --> 02:01:30,146
- He probably will be.
- Absolutely adorable.

942
02:01:30,217 --> 02:01:32,048
- Mummy, are you sure I'm allowed this?
- Yes, yes.

943
02:01:32,118 --> 02:01:34,951
- Yes, of course you are.
- You haven't had any for months.

944
02:01:35,021 --> 02:01:36,420
I'd get it down you now, while you can.

945
02:01:36,489 --> 02:01:37,786
Isn't he handsome?
My God, he's handsome.

946
02:01:37,857 --> 02:01:40,018
Bet you any money
the next one's a girl.

947
02:01:42,162 --> 02:01:43,561
What are you saying about him?

948
02:01:43,630 --> 02:01:45,655
I was just saying he's got
the most adorable cheeks.

949
02:01:45,732 --> 02:01:49,691
We were just saying how handsome he is.
Just so extraordinarily handsome.

950
02:01:49,769 --> 02:01:51,031
I wonder what he's thinking.

951
02:01:51,104 --> 02:01:52,366
Well, you know, they said
he was a thinker. The nurses.

952
02:01:52,439 --> 02:01:54,100
- Deep thoughts. Deep thoughts.
- Here we are.

953
02:01:54,174 --> 02:01:56,108
- To Terence.
- To Terence.

954
02:01:56,176 --> 02:01:58,838
- To Terence.
- And all that sail on him.

955
